description.narrative: During 2021, UNICEF was the main provider of ARVs in pediatric formulation, reaching 1,022 children and adolescents under 15 years of age, beneficiaries of the National HIV/AIDS/STI Program, with the full treatment according to its schedule for 1 year. The Global AIDS Monitoring Report showed that all seropositive children under 15 years of age in the National Program received their ART.UNICEF promoted and strengthened the PTMTC through the acquisition and distribution of 67,000 rapid HIV/syphilis tests for ANC, supplies donation for DNA PCR sampling in high-risk children, and acquisition of ARVs for application during obstetric care | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/01/2022
